Session prompts that produced this change (verbatim user messages):

1. "Ok, I would now like to plan out a new feature. I would like to have a hotkey
   that opens up and 'reading pane' on the bottom half of the screen that shows the
   item detail (like hitting enter does now). Seeing in the reading pane marks it as
   read. Hitting the hotkey again hides the reading pane. Can you plan that out?"

   Plan-mode AskUserQuestion answers:
   - Pane behavior: "Follow selection (live)" — the pane always mirrors the selected
     row; moving the cursor updates the pane and marks that item read.
   - Pane scrolling: "Enter for full reader" — the pane is preview-only; long
     articles are read by promoting to the existing full-screen reader.

2. "/review" — ran the four-reviewer pass (functional, code-quality, adr-compliance,
   performance) on the working-tree changes.

   Review found and I fixed:
   - CRITICAL (perf+functional): rapid scrolling with the pane open spawned
     concurrent r.Render calls on render.Renderer, documented as "not safe for
     concurrent use" — a data race the sequential tests never exercised. Fixed by
     (a) adding a mutex to render.Renderer serializing Render/SetWidth (with a
     16-goroutine race test) and (b) coalescing preview renders single-flight via a
     `loading` gate with a trailing-edge re-load.
   - HIGH (functional): under an unread-only filter the live pane desynced because
     marking the previewed row read removed it from the list. Fixed by skipping
     RemoveLocal while the pane is open (row dims in place; reconciles on reload);
     pane-closed removal preserved.
   - MEDIUM/LOW polish: strengthened the toggle-open test to assert the store
     effect; tied minSplitHeight's comment to reader.headerLines; corrected a
     "not safe for concurrent use" doc contradiction after adding the mutex; added
     an ordering comment to the test fixture.
   Re-review verdicts after fixes: functional APPROVED, code-quality PASS,
   performance PASS, adr-compliance N/A (catalog is cloud/Lambda/React-scoped).

3. "/trueup" — "ok. Please commit your work, add prompts in this session to the
